\begin_layout Standard
Problem 8 [8 Points] 
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
[8 Points] Application of a pseudo random number generator.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x_{t+1}=(a*x_{t}+b)(modm)
\]

\end_inset

Assume that a, and b are constants.
 Then for 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in\{0,1\}$
\end_inset

, create a system of linear congruent equations to solve for a, and b.
 Then, repeast the process for 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in\{2,3\}$
\end_inset

, creating another system of equations.
 Since m is prime it is known that there will be a solution for all possible
 t.
 Compare your values from the two sets of linear system solutions.
 If they agree, or come reasonably close to agreeing, then you can guess
 your opponents hand for 
\begin_inset Formula $t\in\{4,5,6,7,8\}$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

